Welcome to the third exciting part of the Language Development in ASD exercise

In this part of the assignment, we try to figure out how a new study should be planned (i.e.how many participants?) in order to have enough power to replicate the findings (ensuring our sample size is adequate, our alpha at 0.05 and our beta at 0.8): 1- if we trust the estimates of the current study. Report the power analysis and comment on what you can (or cannot) use its estimates for. 2- if we are skeptical of the current study. Report the power analysis and comment on what you can (or cannot) use its estimates for. 3- if we only have access to 30 participants. Identify the power for each relevant effect and discuss whether its worth to run the study and why The list above is also what you should discuss in your code-less report.

Learning objectives

  • Learn how to calculate statistical power
  • Critically appraise how to apply frequentist statistical power

Exercise 1

How much power does your study have (if your model estimates are quite right)? - Load your dataset (both training and testing), fit your favorite model, assess power for your effects of interest (probably your interactions).
